%h3 Secrets
%p A generic container is used for any type of container that a user may wish to create. There are no restrictions on the type or amount of secrets that can be held within a container:

= f.simple_fields_for :secrets, wrapper: :horizontal_form do |secret|

  = secret.input :generic, label: "All secrets", as: :select,
  collection: @secrets.map{|secret|["#{secret.display_name} (created: #{date_humanize(secret.created)}, type: #{secret.secret_type}, status: #{secret.status})", {name: secret.name, secret_ref: secret.secret_ref}.to_json]},
  input_html: { multiple: "multiple", data: {toggle: 'selectMultiple'}}